## Installation

This study tries to answer the Research Question: To what extent have Boston food safety inspection outcomes changed over time in terms of volume and severity, and are certain neighborhoods improving or worsening over the past 20 years?

This study was done for the final project of the Data Scinec major Captsone. 

# Data

The data used is [Food Establishment Inspections Boston Data](https://data.boston.gov/dataset/food-establishment-inspections), and was extracted initially on February 15 2026.

GitHub allows 25MB csv file uploads, so in the "Data" folder you will find 15 subsets that make up the total data set. If you download all 15 subsets, the code in FinalProjectRunningNotebook Jupyter Nitebook file will combine the 15 subsets on its own (there are no additional steps apart from having the 15 subsets and that Jupyter file). 

## Usage

In the files you will find a FinalProjectRunningNotebook Jupyter notebook with the code to run both the analysis, model, and all the graphics generated. (InitialExplorationCleaning(HW7) is not needed for this study, it is simply a marker for keeping track of process, all final data exploration and cleaning required for the study is included in the final file)

PosterDS340H_CélesteDeudon26 is the final poster for the DS Capstone Presentation (presented on April 28th 2026) to show findings and process.

